SD=ECM-DCM
CR= ECM-DCM Fulfillment Arrangement
BQs=InstrumentDefinition Prospectus Placement    
The service domain provides fulfillment services for the issuance of primary market equity and debt capital market instruments for corporate customers. It supports both private and public (IPO) placements and covers the specification, pricing and placement activities associated with issuance. (it does not include secondary market trading of the instrument)
A corporate customer raises capital through issuing corporate debt in the private capital markets
Supports the specification, pricing and issuance of equity and debt (bond) capital market primary market products for corporate financing services
CR - ECM-DCM Fulfillment Arrangement					BQ 1 - Instrument Definition			BQ 2 - Prospectus			BQ 3 - Placement		
In	Up	Ec	Rq	Re	Up	Rq	Re	Up	Rq	Re	Up	Rq	Re
InCR initiate an ECM-DCM transaction for a corporate customer
UpCR Update details of an active ECM-DCM transaction
EcCR Accept, reject, verify, etc. aspects of an ECM-DCM transaction
RqCR Request manual intervention to an active ECM-DCM transaction (e.g. schedule investor discussions)
ReCR Retrieve details about an active ECM-DCM transaction
UpBQ Update details of the ECM-DCM instrument specification
RqBQ Request manual intervention to the instrument definition (e.g. request changes for compliance)
ReBQ Retrieve details about the ECM-DCM instrument definition
UpBQ Update details of the ECM-DCM prospectus
RqBQ Request manual intervention with the prospectus development
ReBQ Retrieve details about the ECM-DCM prospectus development
UpBQ Update details of ECM-DCM placement activity
RqBQ Request manual intervention in the placement activity (e.g. propose prospects)
ReBQ Retrieve details about the ECM-DCM placement actions